				\begin{document} $$  Sensitivity = \frac{TP}{TP+FN}  $$ \end{document}Sensitivity=TPTP+FN

Additionally, we report the F1 measure (Eq. 3), which combines sensitivity and precision. 
3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document} $$  \begin{aligned} F1 & = 2 \times \frac{Precision \times Sensitivity}{Precision+Sensitivity}\\ & = \frac{2 TP}{2 TP + FP + FN}\\ \end{aligned}  $$ \end{document}F1=2×Precision×SensitivityPrecision+Sensitivity=2TP2TP+FP+FN

Comparing the F1 measure to the accuracy (Eq. 4) shows how similar these two measures are. 
4\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
